The following are major news items in leading Pakistani newspapers today:
The News -- Pakistani Foreign Minister Sardar Aseff Ahmed Ali said
Wednesday that Pakistan would respond to India's offer for resumption of
talks within next ten days. The Nation -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari said Wednesday that Pakistan needs to develop an institutional
framework to overcome the crisis in the cotton trade in the country. The
Muslim -- Afghanistan's new Prime Minister Gulbuddin Hekmatyar Wednesday
pledged to protect civilians from official crime and corruption. The
Frontier Post -- Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto has decided to
give a free hand to law enforcing agencies in Punjab province of Pakistan
to stem bomb blasts and other terrorist activities.
